docs {
  # Delete Node Connection

  Soft-delete a node connection and cascade-delete all edges between the two nodes' ports.

  ## Path Parameters
  - `graph_id` (required): UUID of the graph
  - `version_id` (required): UUID of the draft version
  - `nc_id` (required): UUID of the node connection

  ## Response (200)
  ```json
  {
    "status": true,
    "result": {"message": "Node connection deleted successfully"}
  }
  ```

  ## Side Effects
  - Dataset columns are synced (add-only) after connection deletion. Disconnecting nodes may expose new input ports, which creates new dataset columns. Existing columns are never deleted.

  ## Errors
  - `400`: Version is not DRAFT
  - `404`: NodeConnection not found or doesn't belong to this version
}
